  "poem": {
    "content": "A glass harbor, where dreams spend,\nAnd shadows own the fading day.\nI cross the threshold, to begin and end,\nWhere even the best words go astray.\n\nMy mind, a walnut, hard to crack,\nHolds pencils dull, and thoughts oblique.\nEquip me, then, to find my track,\nBefore my spirit starts to leak.\n\nThe ocean’s range, a siren call,\nA zero hour, now fully here.\nI feel the claw of something small,\nA hidden truth, a rising fear.\n\nSubmit myself, to what must be,\nThis Soda fountain's fizzy haze.\nAn aerobic rush, consuming me,\nIn fractured nights and sunlit days.\n\nNo harbor’s charm can make amends,\nUntil the past is left behind.\nThe present then forever mends,\nAnd a new world can I then find",
